# PlaceCardView

## Summary

Renders a wedding place card: an optional uppercase event-title kicker, the guest name in large serif type, an accent rule, then the table name and an optional italic message, with an optional `@logoUrl` event logo as a faint centered watermark behind the content. It is the planner's stationery visual — the print sheet renders one per seated guest, so what prints matches this component exactly. Colors and fonts flow from the theme's semantic tokens with Parisian fallbacks. Sizing is container-query driven, and the guest name auto-fits its width by character count (the print sheet is hidden on screen, so real measurement isn't possible), so the same component reads well as a large isolated card, a small fitted tile, or a print-sheet cell.

## Import

```js
import { PlaceCardView } from '../components/card-views';
```

## Template Usage

As rendered on the planner's print sheet (all args optional; the name falls back to "Guest Name", and `@message` adds an italic closing line):

```gjs
<PlaceCardView
  @eventTitle={{@model.eventTitle}}
  @guestName={{g.fullName}}
  @tableName={{row.table.name}}
  @logoUrl={{this.eventLogoURL}}
/>
```
